ayed on the Sphere arena ahead of Super Bowl LVIII in Las Vegas, Nevada on February 7, 2024.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dIHIgzAUM2BLHmX9_wf_st0Q0B0=/0x2:4994x3331/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73122161/1986209650.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by PATRICK T. FALLON/AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jLQYL9\">You don\u2019t need to sign up for a pricey cable package just to watch the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24064740/super-bowl-2024-best-ads-trailers\">Super Bowl</a> this Sunday. Plenty of streaming services from <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fubo.tv%2Fstream%2Fnfl%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F2%2F8%2F24065543%2Fparamount-plus-showtime-super-bowl-deal-sale\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Fubo</a> to <a href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/li", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T14:30:00+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24064662/linxura-smart-controller-review", "title": "This iPod-like button could be a great\u00a0smart home\u00a0controller", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<p>With customizable icons and an intuitive click wheel, the Linxura solves a big problem with smart buttons. But it needs to dial up its integrations before it\u2019s worth your money. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24064662/linxura-smart-controller-review\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T14:00:00+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24063809/tiktok-shop-product-discovery-fail-videos", "title": "Is this image a pair of shoes or a sponge? TikTok isn\u2019t sure", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Street Style - Day 1 - Seoul Fashion Week F/W 2024\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/V7sEQP2zJ2sBwjEQZ_5pahm3EII=/1x0:4000x2666/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73121863/1968673442.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Jean Chung / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"TQKJ46\">TikTok isn\u2019t just a place to offload your celebrity opinions, give strangers a complete home tour, or share a DIY hack. Each video \u2014 at least in TikTok\u2019s view \u2014 is also a possible advertisement.</p>\n<p id=\"iE3y0K\">As I was scrolling through my feed this week, a video from an account I don\u2019t follow popped up discussing actor Hunter Schafer\u2019s Grammys afterparty outfit. The account has a modest 43,000 followers, and the video has less than 8,000 views. It followed the typical outfit breakdown format: identifying the designer of Schafer\u2019s dress, showing a few different angles, and adding close-up shots of her shoes.</p>\n<p id=\"cV8oD9\">As the video", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T13:00:00+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24065553/google-gemini-ios-android-app-duet-bard", "title": "Google\u2019s AI now goes by a new name: Gemini", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Google logo sits at the center of ominous concentric circles\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qnnRAbPf8Zdm_RXSMyK-1uQKevE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73121711/acastro_180427_1777_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QfptVz\">Google is famous for having a million similar products with confusingly different names and seemingly nothing in common. (Can I interest you in a messaging app?) But when it comes to its AI work, going forward there is only one name that matters: Gemini.</p>\n<p id=\"PtCqX5\">The company <a href=\"https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-gemini-update-sundar-pichai-2024/\">announced on Thursday</a> that it is renaming <a href=\"https://bard.google.com/\">its Bard chatbot</a> to <a href=\"https://gemini.google.com/\">Gemini</a>, releasing a <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.apps.bard", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T12:55:48+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24065866/apple-windows-apps-music-tv-devices-itunes", "title": "Apple moves away from iTunes on PC with new Windows apps", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the Apple logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/o2vMPlVVTGOn91abQM5CGvHm_EI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73121702/STK071_ACastro_apple_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vgJUei\">Apple is officially launching its <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fapps.microsoft.com%2Fdetail%2F9NM4T8B9JQZ1%3Flaunch%3Dtrue%26hl%3Den-us%26gl%3DUS&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F2%2F8%2F24065866%2Fapple-windows-apps-music-tv-devices-itunes\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Apple TV</a>, <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fapps.microsoft.com%2Fdetail%2F9PFHDD62MXS1%3Flaunch%3Dtrue%26hl%3Den-us%26gl%3DUS&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F2%2F8%2F24065866", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T12:37:37+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24065865/ios-17-4-facetime-video-emoji-reaction-api-disable-default", "title": "iOS 17.4 could fix Apple\u2019s awkward video reactions feature", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing Apple\u2019s fireworks reaction on a video call.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/h_1wNIi_MLKdoe4-MOevmq53Uvk=/0x0:1000x667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73121692/macos_sonoma_video_gesture_fireworks_two_thumbs_up.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The animations are fine for FaceTime, but maybe not a therapy telehealth app.</em> | Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KSWVJy\">Apple looks ready to give developers more control over its video emoji reactions feature in upcoming iOS 17.4 and iPadOS 17.4 updates, <a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/02/07/apple-api-for-turning-off-3d-gesture-effects/\"><em>MacRumors</em> reports</a>. The feature, which was introduced with the release of iOS 17 and iPadOS 17 last year (as well as in macOS 14), automatically shows 3D animations like <a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/how-to/use-reaction-effects-facetime/\">fireworks and lasers</a> when an Apple device\u2019s came", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T10:07:28+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24065809/meta-european-union-digital-services-act-monitoring-compliance-charge-challenge", "title": "Meta\u2019s not happy with its bill for enforcing the EU\u2019s tough new DSA", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Meta logo on a red background with repeating black icons, giving a squiggly effect.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6yndciKYDTW9o-L4PRwcUoToy40=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73121462/STK043_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_3_Meta.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ah6daE\">Meta is challenging a fee it must pay EU regulators tasked with enforcing tough new content moderation rules required by the Digital Services Act (DSA), <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/meta-challenges-supervisory-fee-eu-online-content-rules-2024-02-07/\"><em>Reuters </em>reports</a>. Although the fee is capped at 0.05 percent of a company\u2019s profits, Meta isn\u2019t happy that loss-making companies won\u2019t have to pay while it\u2019s on the hook for a reported \u20ac11 million.</p>\n<p id=\"k0MfpE\">\u201cWe disagree with the methodology used to calculate these fees,\u201d Meta\u2019s EMEA policy comms spoke", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T09:26:50+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24057965/qi2-car-charger-esr-review-price-specs", "title": "ESR Qi2 wireless car charger review: goodbye Mag$afe", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<p>It\u2019s just as fast, the magnet is just as strong, but it costs half as much as those proprietary Apple mounts.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24057965/qi2-car-charger-esr-review-price-specs\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating_visits": 0, "artist": null, "tags": [], "dead": false, "age": null}, {"page_rating_votes": 0, "thumbnail": null, "bookmarked": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "vote": 0, "permanent": false, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "date_published": "2024-02-08T00:18:07+00:00", "language": "en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/7/24065332/denmark-google-student-data-collection-privacy", "title": "Google\u2019s use of student data could effectively ban Chromebooks from Denmark schools", "album": "", "page_rating": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Google\u2019s wordmark, written in red and pink on a dark blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RzDuqM3yN_xngxmJpW-dEl10Uog=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73120813/STK093_Google_06.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"o2zn3R\">Danish privacy regulator Datatilsysnet has ruled that cities in Denmark need considerably more assurances about privacy to use Google service that may ex